<subSubSection pageId="2" pageNumber="59" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="2.[151,1436,1633,1968]" pageId="2" pageNumber="59">
This species was described by 
<bibRefCitation author="Steinheil" box="[479,651,1633,1656]" pageId="2" pageNumber="60" refString="Steinheil, E. (1872) Symbolae ad historiam Coleopterorum Argentinae meridionalis, ossia enumerazione dei coleotteri raccolti dal Prof. Strobel, durante il suo soggiorno in Buenos Aires e nei viaggi de la intrapresi a Mendoza e nal Chili, indi a Bahia Blanca ed al Carmen de los Patagones; e descrizione delle specie nuove. Atti della Societa Italiana di Scienze Naturali, 15, 554 - 578." type="journal article" year="1872">
Steinheil (
<number box="[588,643,1633,1656]" pageId="2" pageNumber="59" value="1872.0">1872</number>
)
</bibRefCitation>
based on a single male and was originally placed in the genus 
<taxonomicName authority="Burmeister, 1847" authorityName="Burmeister" authorityYear="1847" class="Insecta" family="Scarabaeidae" genus="Scaptophilus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="59" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="59">Scaptophilus</emphasis>
Burmeister, 
<number box="[321,377,1668,1691]" pageId="2" pageNumber="59" value="1847.0">1847</number>
</taxonomicName>
, which was later synonymized with 
<taxonomicName authority="Hope, 1837" authorityName="Hope" authorityYear="1837" box="[770,1005,1668,1691]" class="Insecta" family="Dynastidae" genus="Bothynus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="59" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[770,869,1668,1691]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="59">Bothynus</emphasis>
Hope, 
<number box="[948,1005,1668,1691]" pageId="2" pageNumber="59" value="1837.0">1837</number>
</taxonomicName>
. 
<bibRefCitation author="Ohaus" box="[1016,1163,1668,1691]" pageId="2" pageNumber="60" refString="Ohaus, F. (1910) Neue Coleoptera Lamellicornia aus Argentinien. Deutsche Entomologische Zeitschrift, 2, 173 - 186." type="journal article" year="1910">
Ohaus (
<number box="[1099,1155,1668,1691]" pageId="2" pageNumber="59" value="1910.0">1910</number>
)
</bibRefCitation>
described the genus 
<taxonomicName class="Insecta" family="Dynastidae" genus="Eremobothynus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="59" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="59">Eremobothynus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
to accommodate this species. 
<bibRefCitation author="Ohaus" box="[602,748,1702,1725]" pageId="2" pageNumber="60" refString="Ohaus, F. (1910) Neue Coleoptera Lamellicornia aus Argentinien. Deutsche Entomologische Zeitschrift, 2, 173 - 186." type="journal article" year="1910">
Ohaus (
<number box="[684,740,1702,1725]" pageId="2" pageNumber="59" value="1910.0">1910</number>
)
</bibRefCitation>
also described the female of 
<taxonomicName box="[1058,1180,1702,1726]" class="Insecta" family="Dynastidae" genus="Eremobothynus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="59" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="cornutus">
<emphasis box="[1058,1074,1703,1726]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="59">E</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis box="[1087,1180,1703,1726]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="59">cornutus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, and mentioned that the three males he studied had a more developed horn than the “female” he examined. It is very probable that he was actually describing a very small male and mistook it for a female.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="2.[151,1436,1633,1968]" pageId="2" pageNumber="59">
During the course of our studies, we examined a large number of male and female specimens of 
<taxonomicName box="[1217,1339,1806,1830]" class="Insecta" family="Dynastidae" genus="Eremobothynus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="59" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="cornutus">
<emphasis box="[1217,1233,1807,1830]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="59">E</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis box="[1246,1339,1807,1830]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="59">cornutus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
from the second author’s collection. All females examined were completely unarmed, with no horns or tubercles on the head (
<figureCitation captionStart="FIGURES 1 – 4" captionStartId="1.[151,269,1954,1978]" captionTargetBox="[302,1290,408,1929]" captionTargetId="figure@1.[292,1296,384,1948]" captionTargetPageId="1" captionText="FIGURES 1 – 4. Eremobothynus spp.: 1 - 2: E. hirsutus sp. nov., holotype, dorsal and lateral views; 3: E. cornutus, male dorsal view; 4: female head and pronotum anterolateral view." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/181375/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="59">
Fig. 
<number box="[151,167,1876,1899]" pageId="2" pageNumber="59" value="4.0">4</number>
</figureCitation>
). Therefore, all identification keys (e.g., 
<bibRefCitation author="Endrodi" box="[602,750,1876,1899]" pageId="2" pageNumber="60" refString="Endrodi, S. (1969) Monographie der Dynastinae, 4. Tribus, amerikanische Pentodontini. Entomologische Abhandlungen Staatliches Museum fur Tierkunde in Dresden, 37, 1 - 145." type="journal article" year="1969">
Endrödi 
<number box="[694,750,1876,1899]" pageId="2" pageNumber="59" value="1969.0">1969</number>
</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation author="Endrodi" box="[761,909,1876,1899]" pageId="2" pageNumber="60" refString="Endrodi, S. (1985) The Dynastinae of the World. Dr. W. Junk Publisher, Dordrecht Netherlands. 800 pp., 46 plates." type="book" year="1985">
Endrödi 
<number box="[853,909,1876,1899]" pageId="2" pageNumber="59" value="1985.0">1985</number>
</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation author="Ratcliffe" box="[919,1074,1876,1899]" pageId="2" pageNumber="60" refString="Ratcliffe, B. C. (1981) Barutus hartmanni, a new genus and species from Panama with a key to the genera of New World Pentodontini (Coleoptera: Scarabaeidae: Dynastinae). Coleopterists Bulletin, 35, 463 - 472." type="journal article" year="1981">
Ratcliffe 
<number box="[1019,1074,1876,1899]" pageId="2" pageNumber="59" value="1981.0">1981</number>
</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation author="Ratcliffe" box="[1085,1339,1876,1899]" pageId="2" pageNumber="60" refString="Ratcliffe, B. C. &amp; Hardy, M. (2005) Collagenus dasysternus, a new genus and species of Dynastinae from eastern Venezuela with a key to the New World genera of Pentodontini (Coleoptera: Scarabaeidae: Dynastinae). Coleopterists Bulletin, 59, 143 - 150." type="journal article" year="2005">
Ratcliffe &amp; Hardy 
<number box="[1284,1339,1876,1899]" pageId="2" pageNumber="59" value="2005.0">2005</number>
</bibRefCitation>
) must be corrected to indicate that only males in 
<taxonomicName box="[593,718,1910,1934]" class="Insecta" family="Dynastidae" genus="Eremobothynus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="59" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="cornutus">
<emphasis box="[593,609,1911,1934]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="59">E</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis box="[625,718,1911,1934]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="59">cornutus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
have a frontal horn (
<figureCitation box="[956,1023,1910,1933]" captionStart="FIGURES 1 – 4" captionStartId="1.[151,269,1954,1978]" captionTargetBox="[302,1290,408,1929]" captionTargetId="figure@1.[292,1296,384,1948]" captionTargetPageId="1" captionText="FIGURES 1 – 4. Eremobothynus spp.: 1 - 2: E. hirsutus sp. nov., holotype, dorsal and lateral views; 3: E. cornutus, male dorsal view; 4: female head and pronotum anterolateral view." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/181375/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="59">
Fig. 
<number box="[1009,1023,1910,1933]" pageId="2" pageNumber="59" value="3.0">3</number>
</figureCitation>
), and that the pronotum is convex in females (
<figureCitation box="[248,312,1945,1968]" captionStart="FIGURES 1 – 4" captionStartId="1.[151,269,1954,1978]" captionTargetBox="[302,1290,408,1929]" captionTargetId="figure@1.[292,1296,384,1948]" captionTargetPageId="1" captionText="FIGURES 1 – 4. Eremobothynus spp.: 1 - 2: E. hirsutus sp. nov., holotype, dorsal and lateral views; 3: E. cornutus, male dorsal view; 4: female head and pronotum anterolateral view." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/181375/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="59">
Fig. 
<number box="[298,312,1945,1968]" pageId="2" pageNumber="59" value="4.0">4</number>
</figureCitation>
) and not declivous as in males.
</paragraph>
